data.text:
Nigeria, March 6 -- Dick Cheney, an American businessman, and politician whose full name is Richard Bruce Cheney has an estimated net worth of $150 million.

Richard Bruce Cheney is a well-known American politician and businessman, who served as the 46th Vice President of the United States from 2001 to 2009 under President George W. Bush. He is currently the oldest living former U.S. Vice President, following the death of Walter Mondale in 2021.

Born on January 30, 1941, in Lincoln, Nebraska, Cheney grew up there and in Casper, Wyoming. He attended Yale University before earning a bachelor of arts and a master of arts in political science from the University of Wyoming.
